messages.messageBody:
I dont think I did an intro here. Sorry Amanda

I am Laura from Maine (someday ill come up with a nickname or a sig line).
My husband Brian is an ASE Mechanic.
I a SAHM and former Tom boy (still kinda<G>), US Marine (had to prove to my
dad that I could take worse than he could dish out),District Manager of 60+
newspaper kids and drivers and owner of a quite successful . Com
CountryMooseKids (which I sank single hand-ed-ly by opening up a store front) Its all a
learning exp..

Our children are Dustin 12 (my 1st son, business assistant and loyal start up
business supporter,shipper,buyer and coworker. Its been a few years but he
was the nuts and bolts of our operation. He is also a handsome young man.
***
Cassidy 4 3/4 years old. She is beautiful,sweet,loving,sensitive and the
daughter that as a tom boy never thought id have. She is blonde haired, loves
barbies,dresses,jeans,cars,caliou,cooking and nurses her baby dolls just like mama.
***
Nicholas 2 years old. Most noticeable are his big bright glowing BLUE eyes
like I have never seen before. Everyone loves his eyes and long eyelashes and he
knows it. He likes to play with his sister and gets sad when she needs
space. See "keeping Peace posts" He likes helping mommy and daddy, cars,
water,trampolines,trikes, and his binky.
***
Cameron 3 mo. Likes to nurse, smile and nurse. He is a very happy baby.
He loves his sister and brothers. He seems to be very giggly for Dustin the
oldest which is really cool because at 12 and 3 mo there isn't much in common.
***
I also have a room booked at the convention in August.
THE END

Laura~Maine
******************************************************************************

<<Thanks for understanding and again, I am soooo sorry that you
misunderstood before. I am still new here and learning who is who,
so may I ask how many youngins you have?

~Amanda>>>
